info:
PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors were developed to transfer high power (500V) in harsh environments with full safety for the user. The circular connectors offer an IP28 rating, tested pressure watertight (48h, under 2m water), and allows a finger test for socket contacts and inserts. Depending on the shell and backshell plating option, the PowerSafe connectors operate in a temperature range as low as -65°C and up to +200°C. The Amphenol Socapex PowerSafe MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors are ideal for use in defense, avionics, and harsh industrial markets.

LJT MIL-DTL-38999 Series I Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace LJT Connectors are subminiature cylindrical connectors qualified to MIL-DTL-38999 Series I. Amphenol Aerospace LJT Connectors provide scoop-proof contact protection and grounding fingers for electromagnetic interference (EMI) shielding. A five key / keyway design eliminates mismating and ensures error-proof alternate positioning. The series is designed for use in commercial and military aerospace applications.

info:
Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps
        
        
            Amphenol Pcd Black-Zinc Nickel-Finish Backshell Clamps are a RoHS compliant replacement for cadmium plating. The black-zinc, nickel-finish clamps are a cost-effective cable holding option over cadmium and offer environmental protection. The series is available in a variety of shell sizes (11 through 48), both military (MIL) specification and commercial types, and with EMI/RFI shielding. The clamps clean-up the cable after termination and provide good strain relief at the termination area. Amphenol Pcd Black Zinc Nickel Finish Backshell Clamps are can be used as a replacement for cadmium plating in aeronautical and military applications.

Circular MIL Spec Connector HERMETIC
info:
Hermetic Circular Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace Hermetic Circular Connectors maintain system integrity in applications where reliability and performance are critical, such as gas-tight barriers or areas with high-pressure differentials. A wide range of materials and manufacturing capabilities are used to provide consumer and MIL-Spec products for glass-to-metal seals and lightweight epoxy backfilled solutions. The epoxy-sealed connectors are a lightweight alternative to glass-sealed hermetic connectors for use in avionics and other weight-sensitive applications where a high level of sealing is required. Epoxy-sealed connectors are an optimal solution when increasingly stringent sealing requirements must be met.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector High Speed 2M801 Plu kel, Anti-Decoupling
info:
2M Micro-Miniature Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace 2M Micro-Miniature Connectors are designed for interconnect applications requiring high performance. These connectors are 71% lighter, 52% smaller, and have 60% more contact density than other connectors in their class. These micro-miniature connectors are designed and tested to Mil-Spec standards and comparable to MIL-DTL-38999 connectors. They are offered in four types: triple-start ACME thread, push-pull, bayonet, and dual-start ACME thread. Amphenol Aerospace 2M Micro-Miniature Connectors are intermountable and intermateable with existing micro-miniature aerospace/defense connectors, including the Glenair Mighty Mouse series. These lightweight, high-density connectors maximize SWaP (size, weight, and power) in a variety of high-reliability, harsh environments.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Recept. Crimp 13cts 10GBit
info:
TV Data Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Air LB Germany TV Data Connectors are MIL-DTL-38999 Series III connectors featuring EMI/RFI protection and high corrosion resistance. These connectors come in nine shell sizes (from 09 to 25) with more than 80 contact arrangements. The TV data connectors feature high-density inserts that are compatible with twinax, coax, and quadrax and the receptacles come with reinforced sealing. The shell material of these connectors are made of Aluminum, stainless steel, and marine bronze. The stainless steel sheet material provides firewall capability and the marine bronze shell provides robustness for marine applications. The TV data connectors plating are made of olive drab cadmium, nickel, passivation, and black zinc nickel. These connectors are capable of quick coupling with mate and self-lock in a 360° turn of the coupling nut and anti-decoupling device for high vibration performance. The EMI/RFI protection is available via shell-to-shell bottoming and grounding fingers on the plug shell.

Circular MIL Spec Contacts OctoMax 1G26 PCB PIN CI D38999
info:
OctoMax 1G26 Contacts
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex OctoMax 1G26 Contacts offer an impedance rating of 100Ω at 100MHz, a rated current of 1A per contact, and a minimum of 500 mating cycles. The contacts feature eight strategically spaced inner contacts that form four 100Ω matched impedance differential pairs, making them equivalent to two quadrax. Amphenol Socapex OctoMax 1G26 Contacts feature a copper alloy body construction and a thermoplastic insulator. They are ideal for Ethernet, ground vehicles, and commercial aerospace applications.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector
info:
D38999 Series III Double Flange Receptacles
        
        
            ITT Cannon D38999 Series III Double Flange Receptacles for PCB mounting are engineered for use in high-vibration, harsh environment applications across the aerospace and defense industry. These robust connectors can attach directly to the connector shell, which improves grounding, reduces contact solder joint stress, and eliminates extra hardware. ITT Cannon D38999 Double Flange Receptacles feature 500 mating cycles and an operating temperature range of -65°C to +200°C. These components offer convenience, performance, and reliability, making them ideal for military aviation, ground transports, commercial aerospace, and communications systems.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector Strt Plug, Elect Ni 6-4, Socket, A Key
info:
MKJ Clip Lock Miniature Circular Connectors
        
        
            ITT Cannon MKJ Clip Lock Miniature Circular Connectors are small, light interconnects with a clip lock latching system for commercial avionics, in-flight entertainment (IFE), city infrastructure, factory equipment, and industrial applications. This robust series is rated to IP67 and offers a snap-on positive lock coupling system that provides secure sealing without requiring additional space commonly required in threaded or bayonet connectors. ITT Cannon MKJ Clip Lock Miniature Circular Connectors operate in harsh environments with five plating options and come with high-density size 23, 20HD, 16, or 12 contacts.

description: Circular MIL Spec Contacts Quadrax Socket conta ct, 100?, 1000 Base-
info:
HS Amphe-Lite Circular MIL-Spec Contacts
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial HS Amphe-Lite Circular MIL-Spec Contacts incorporates high-speed contacts into Amphe-Lite housing, providing datalink solutions. The Amphe-Lite offers high-data transfer rates, excellent EMI compatibility, and lower power consumption rates. These connectors are available in Differential Quadrax Contacts and Split Pair Quadrax Contacts variants. The Amphe-Lite connectors are designed for high-speed signal applications in ruggedized and high vibration environments. This includes two pairs (4 pins) of high-speed contacts having bandwidth up to 3.125GHz, Ethernet Bas-T-100Ω, and a data rate of up to 6.5Gbps. The Amphe-Lite Quadrax features rear-release contacts, front and rear mount, and EMI- shielding. These connectors come with two Ohm matched impedance differential pairs, available in size 8 crimp termination or PC trails. The Amphe-Lite circular MIL-Spec contacts require modification of the MIL-DTL-38999 connector to accommodate keyed contacts.
